Name: kAnimatedImageResume
Documentation:
Uses the Resume method instead of the Catch-up method for animated images.
- Catch-up behavior tries to keep animated images in pace with wall-clock
  time. This might require decoding several animation frames if the
  animation has fallen behind.
- Resume behavior presents what would have been the next presented frame.
  This means it might only decode one frame, resuming where it left off.
  However, if the animation updates faster than the display's refresh rate,
  it is possible to decode more than a single frame.

BFCache of all pages when the system is under memory pressure.

Name: kBackForwardCache
Documentation: Enable using the BackForwardCache.

Name: kBackForwardCacheABExperimentControl
Documentation:
The "BackForwardCacheABExperimentControl" feature indicates the state of the
same-site BackForwardCache experiment. This information is used when sending
the "Sec-bfcache-experiment" HTTP Header on resource requests. The header
value is determined by the value of the "experiment_group_for_http_header"
feature parameter.

Name: kBackForwardCacheDedicatedWorker
Documentation:
Allows pages with DedicatedWorker to stay eligible for the back/forward
cache.

Name: kBackForwardCacheMediaSessionPlaybackStateChange
Documentation:
Allows pages with MediaSession's playback state change to stay eligible for
the back/forward cache.

Name: kBackForwardCacheMediaSessionService
Documentation:
Allows pages that created a MediaSession service to stay eligible for the
back/forward cache.

Name: kBackForwardCacheMemoryControls
Documentation:
BackForwardCacheMemoryControls is enabled only on Android to disable
BackForwardCache for lower memory devices due to memory limiations.

Name: kBackForwardCacheNoTimeEviction
Documentation:
Removes the time limit for cached content. This is used on bots to identify
accidentally passing tests.

Name: kBackForwardCacheSameSiteForBots
Documentation:
Enable same-site back-forward cache for trybots. This is here because of
https://crbug.com/1211818 and should only used for trybots. For normal use
cases, please set BackForwardCache's enable_same_site param to true.

Name: kBackfaceVisibilityInterop
Documentation:
When enabled, enforces new interoperable semantics for 3D transforms.
See crbug.com/1008483.

Name: kBackgroundFetch
Documentation: Kill switch for Background Fetch.

Name: kBackgroundMediaRendererHasModerateBinding
Documentation:
Sets moderate binding to background renderers playing media, when enabled.
Else the renderer will have strong binding.

Name: kBackgroundTracingPerformanceMark
Documentation:
Used to configure a per-origin allowlist of performance.mark events that are
permitted to be included in slow reports traces. See crbug.com/1181774.

Name: kBackgroundVideoPauseOptimization
Documentation: Let video without audio be paused when it is playing in the background.

Name: kBestEffortPriorityForAdFrame
Documentation: Enables setting the priority of an ad frame to best effort priority.

Name: kBestEffortPriorityForBackgroundPages
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of background (with no audio) pages'
task queues to best effort.

Name: kBetterTelemetryAcrossReports
Documentation:
Enables including some information in protection requests sent to Safe
Browsing.

Name: kBigLittleScheduling
Documentation:
Takes advantage of specifying which big.LITTLE cores to schedule different
threads on. Note this conflicts with PowerScheduler feature.

Name: kBindingManagementWaiveCpu
Documentation:
If enabled, BindingManager will use Context.BIND_NOT_FOREGROUND to avoid
affecting cpu scheduling priority.

Name: kBiometricTouchToFill
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kBlinkCompositorUseDisplayThreadPriority
Documentation:
Controls whether we use ThreadPriority::DISPLAY for renderer
compositor & IO threads.

Name: kBlinkHeapCompaction
Documentation: Blink garbage collection.

Name: kBlinkHeapConcurrentMarking
Documentation: Enables concurrently marking Blink's heap.

Name: kBlinkHeapConcurrentSweeping
Documentation: Enables concurrently sweeping Blink's heap.

Name: kBlinkHeapIncrementalMarking
Documentation: Enables incrementally marking Blink's heap.

Name: kBlinkHeapIncrementalMarkingStress
Documentation:
Enables a marking stress mode that schedules more garbage collections and
also adds additional verification passes.

Name: kBlockCrossOriginTopNavigationToDiffentScheme
Documentation:
Kill switch for the blocking of the navigation of top from a cross origin
iframe to a different scheme. TODO(https://crbug.com/1151507): Remove in
M92.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, private network requests initiated from
non-secure contexts in the `public` address space  are blocked.

See also:
 - https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#integration-fetch
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromPrivate
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsForNavigations

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsDeprecationTrial
Documentation:
Enables use of the PrivateNetworkAccessNonSecureContextsAllowed deprecation
trial. This is a necessary yet insufficient condition: documents that wish to
make use of the trial must additionally serve a valid origin trial token.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsForNavigations
Documentation:
When both kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsForNavigations and
kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests are enabled, navigations initiated
by documents in a less-private network may only target a more-private network
if the initiating context is secure.

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromPrivate
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, requests to localhost initiated from non-secure
contexts in the `private` IP address space are blocked.

See also:
 - https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#integration-fetch
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests

Name: kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequestsFromUnknown
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, requests to localhost initiated from non-secure
contexts in the `unknown` IP address space are blocked.

See also:
 - kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests

Name: kBlockPromptsIfDismissedOften
Documentation:
Enables or disables whether permission prompts are automatically blocked
after the user has explicitly dismissed them too many times.

Name: kBlockPromptsIfIgnoredOften
Documentation:
Enables or disables whether permission prompts are automatically blocked
after the user has ignored them too many times.

Name: kBlockRepeatedNotificationPermissionPrompts
Documentation:
Once the user declines a notification permission prompt in a WebContents,
automatically dismiss subsequent prompts in the same WebContents, from any
origin, until the next user-initiated navigation.

Name: kBlockingDownloadsInAdFrameWithoutUserActivation
Documentation:
Enable intervention for download that was initiated from or occurred in an ad
frame without user activation.

Name: kBlockingFocusWithoutUserActivation
Documentation:
Enabled to block programmatic focus in subframes when not triggered by user
activation (see htpps://crbug.com/954349).

Name: kBookmarkPaths
Documentation:
If enabled, inputs may match bookmark paths. These path matches won't
contribute to scoring. E.g. 'planets jupiter' can suggest a bookmark titled
'Jupiter' with URL 'en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jupiter' located in a path
containing 'planet.'

Name: kBookmarksExportUseSaf
Documentation: disabled by default because of an issue on Android 6.0

Name: kBresenhamCadence
Documentation:
Makes VideoCadenceEstimator use Bresenham-like algorithm for frame cadence
estimations.

Name: kBrowserUseDisplayThreadPriority
Documentation: Use ThreadPriority::DISPLAY for browser UI and IO threads.

Name: kBrowserVerifiedUserActivationKeyboard
Documentation: When enabled, keyboard user activation will be verified by the browser side.

Name: kBrowserVerifiedUserActivationMouse
Documentation: When enabled, mouse user activation will be verified by the browser side.

Name: kCOEPForSharedWorker
Documentation: Support COEP on SharedWorker.

Name: kCORBProtectionSniffing
Documentation:
When kCORBProtectionSniffing is enabled CORB sniffs additional same-origin
resources if they look sensitive.

Name: kCORSErrorsIssueOnly
Documentation:
Suppresses console errors for CORS problems which report an associated
inspector issue anyway.

Name: kCSSCascadeLayers
Documentation: https://drafts.csswg.org/css-cascade-5/#layering

Name: kCSSContainerQueries
Documentation: Enable CSS Container Queries. Also implies LayoutNGGrid and CSSContainSize1D.

Name: kCacheControlNoStoreEnterBackForwardCache
Documentation:
Allows pages with cache-control:no-store to enter the back/forward cache.
Feature params can specify whether pages with cache-control:no-store can be
restored if cookies change / if HTTPOnly cookies change.
TODO(crbug.com/1228611): Enable this feature.

Name: kCacheInlineScriptCode
Documentation: Enables code caching for inline scripts.

Name: kCacheStorageCodeCacheHintHeader
Documentation:
When enabled allows the header name used in the blink
CacheStorageCodeCacheHint runtime feature to be modified.  This runtime
feature disables generating full code cache for responses stored in
cache_storage during a service worker install event.  The runtime feature
must be enabled via the blink runtime feature mechanism, however.

Name: kCacheStorageParallelOps
Documentation:
Enables support for parallel cache_storage operations via the
"max_shared_ops" fieldtrial parameter.

Name: kCanPlayHls
Documentation:
Enables CanPlayType() (and other queries) for HLS MIME types. Note that
disabling this also causes navigation to .m3u8 files to trigger downloading
instead of playback.

Name: kCanvas2DImageChromium
Documentation:
If Canvas2D Image Chromium is allowed, this feature controls whether it is
enabled.

Name: kCanvasOopRasterization
Documentation: Enables the use of out of process rasterization for canvas.

Name: kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin
Documentation:
When kCapReferrerToOriginOnCrossOrigin is enabled, HTTP referrers on cross-
origin requests are restricted to contain at most the source origin.

Name: kCastDeviceFilter
Documentation: Used in downstream code.

Name: kCategoricalSearch
Documentation: Enables categorical search in the launcher.

Name: kCdmHostVerification
Documentation:
CDM host verification is enabled by default. Can be disabled for testing.
Has no effect if ENABLE_CDM_HOST_VERIFICATION buildflag is false.

Name: kCdmProcessSiteIsolation
Documentation:
Use per-CDM-type, per-user and per-site CDM processes (for library CDM). If
disabled, the CDM processes are only per-CDM-type, meaning different sites
using the same CDM type would share one CDM process.

Name: kCertificateTransparency2022Policy
Documentation:
If enabled, the 2022 CT policy which removes the one Google log
requirement, introduces log operator diversity requirements, and increases
the number of embedded SCTs required for certificates with a lifetime over
180 days (from 2 to 3) will be used for any certificate issued after February
1, 2022.

Name: kCertificateTransparency2022PolicyAllCerts
Documentation:
If enabled, the 2022 CT policy which removes the one Google log
requirement, introduces log operator diversity requirements, and increases
the number of embedded SCTs required for certificates with a lifetime over
180 days (from 2 to 3) will be used for all certificates.

Name: kCertificateTransparencyAndroid
Documentation: Enables Certificate Transparency on Android.

Name: kChangeDiskCacheSizeExperiment
Documentation:
Experiment to increase the cache size to see the impact on various
performance metrics.

Name: kChangePictureVideoMode
Documentation: Enables change picture video mode.

Name: kChangeServiceWorkerPriorityForClientForegroundStateChange
Documentation:
Controls whether service worker process priority is affected by client
process fore/background state change.

Name: kCheckCacheForQueuedRequests
Documentation:
Check disk cache to see if the queued requests (especially those don't need
validation) have already been cached. If yes, start them as they may not
contend for network.

Name: kCheckOfflineCapability
Documentation:
Dispatches a fake fetch event to a service worker to check the offline
capability of the site before promoting installation.
See https://crbug.com/965802 for more details.

Name: kChromeLabs
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kChromeManagementPageAndroid
Documentation: Enable chrome://management page on Android.

Name: kClearCrossSiteCrossBrowsingContextGroupWindowName
Documentation:
Clear the window.name property for the top-level cross-site navigations that
swap BrowsingContextGroups(BrowsingInstances).

Name: kClientHintThirdPartyDelegation
Documentation: Allow third-party delegation of client hint information.

Name: kClientHintsDPR
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-dpr` client hint.

Name: kClientHintsDPR_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `dpr` client hint.

Name: kClientHintsDeviceMemory
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-device-memory` client hint.

Name: kClientHintsDeviceMemory_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `device-memory` client hint.

Name: kClientHintsMetaHTTPEquivAcceptCH
Documentation: Allow use of an http-equiv meta tag to set client hints.

Name: kClientHintsMetaNameAcceptCH
Documentation: Allow use of a named meta tag to set client hints.

Name: kClientHintsResourceWidth
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-width` client hint.

Name: kClientHintsResourceWidth_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `width` client hint.

Name: kClientHintsViewportWidth
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-viewport-width` client hint.

Name: kClientHintsViewportWidth_DEPRECATED
Documentation: Enable legacy `viewport-width` client hint.

Name: kClientSideDetectionDocumentScanning
Documentation: Controls whether Office documents will be scanned using //third_party maldoca

Name: kClientSideDetectionForAndroid
Documentation: Enables client side detection on Android.

Name: kClientSideDetectionModelHighMemoryTag
Documentation:
Determines the tag to pass to Omaha to get a client side detection model.
This is used for high-memory devices, when `kClientSideDetectionModelTag` is
disabled.

Name: kClientSideDetectionModelIsFlatBuffer
Documentation: The client side detection model is a flatbuffer.

Name: kClientSideDetectionModelTag
Documentation: Determines the tag to pass to Omaha to get a client side detection model.

Name: kClientSideDetectionModelVersion
Documentation:
Determines the experimental version of client side detection model, for
Desktop.

Name: kClientSideDetectionReferrerChain
Documentation: Enables client side detection referrer chain.

Name: kClipboardCustomFormats
Documentation:
Allows read/write of custom formats with unsanitized clipboard content. See
crbug.com/106449.

Name: kClipboardSuggestionContentHidden
Documentation:
If enabled, clipboard suggestion will not show the clipboard content until
the user clicks the reveal button.

Name: kClobberTriggersContextualWebZeroSuggest
Documentation: On-Focus Suggestions a.k.a. ZeroSuggest.

Name: kClobberTriggersSRPZeroSuggest
Documentation:
If enabled, when the user clears the whole omnibox text (i.e. via Backspace),
Chrome will request remote ZeroSuggest suggestions for the SRP (search
results page).

Name: kClosedTabCache
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kCodeCacheDeletionWithoutFilter
Documentation: When enabled, code cache does not use a browsing_data filter for deletions.

Name: kColorProviderRedirectionForThemeProvider
Documentation:
Whether or not to delegate color queries from the ThemeProvider to the
ColorProvider.

Name: kCompactIDBOnClose
Documentation:
This is an emergency kill switch to use with Finch if the feature needs to be
shut off.

Name: kCompositorThreadedScrollbarScrolling
Documentation: Keep sorted!

Name: kCompressParkableStrings
Documentation:
Disabling this will cause parkable strings to never be compressed.
This is useful for headless mode + virtual time. Since virtual time advances
quickly, strings may be parked too eagerly in that mode.

Name: kComputeAXMode
Documentation:
Compute the AXMode based on AccessibilityServiceInfo. If disabled,
the AXMode is either entirely on or entirely off.

Name: kComputePressure
Documentation: Kill switch for the Compute Pressure API. https://crbug.com/1067627

Name: kConfirmSuggestionRemovals
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values in
the .cc file.

Name: kConnectorsScanningReportOnlyUI
Documentation:
Controls the non-blocking scanning UI for Connectors scanning requests. If
this is enabled, the downloaded file(s) will be renamed immediately and the
scanning will take place without UI when the policy is set to "non-blocking"
instead of just showing an "Open Now" button with the blocking UI.

Name: kConsolidatedMovementXY
Documentation: When enabled, event.movement is calculated in blink instead of in browser.

Name: kConsumeCodeCacheOffThread
Documentation: Controls off-thread code cache consumption.

Name: kContentCaptureConstantStreaming
Documentation: Enables the constant streaming in the ContentCapture task.

Name: kContentCaptureInWebLayer
Documentation:
ContentCapture in WebLayer, this flag is independent from the kContentCapture
flag.

Name: kContentCaptureTriggeringForExperiment
Documentation:
ContentCapture is triggered in the unpredictable conditions which might be
changed on different aiai release or configuration push, this feature allows
us to trigger the ContentCapture independently to get the unbiased result.

Name: kContentLanguagesInLanguagePicker
Documentation: This feature enables an intent that starts translating the foreground tab.

Name: kContextMenuPerformanceInfoAndRemoteHintFetching
Documentation:
Enables performance info in the context menu and fetching from a remote
Optimization Guide Service.

Name: kConversionMeasurement
Documentation: Controls whether the Conversion Measurement API infrastructure is enabled.

Name: kConversionMeasurementAPIAlternativeUsage
Documentation:
Field trial feature for controlling usage restriction of the
Conversion Measurement API's origin trial tokens. When disabled, the API
cannot be enabled by tokens using the user subset usage restriction.

Name: kCookieSameSiteConsidersRedirectChain
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, redirected requests will be considered
cross-site for the purpose of SameSite cookies if any redirect hop was
cross-site to the target URL, even if the original initiator of the
redirected request was same-site with the target URL (and the
site-for-cookies).
See spec changes in https://github.com/httpwg/http-extensions/pull/1348

Name: kCooperativeScheduling
Documentation: Enables Blink cooperative scheduling.

Name: kCorsNonWildcardRequestHeadersSupport
Documentation: https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#cors-non-wildcard-request-header-name

Name: kCpuAffinityRestrictToLittleCores
Documentation:
Features supported for legacy reasons.
TODO(eseckler): Remove once use cases for these have been migrated.

Name: kCrashReporting
Documentation:
Enables crash reporting via Reporting API.
https://www.w3.org/TR/reporting/#crash-report

Name: kCriticalClientHint
Documentation:
Enables support for the `Critical-CH` response header.
https://github.com/WICG/client-hints-infrastructure/blob/master/reliability.md#critical-ch

Name: kCrossOriginEmbedderPolicyCredentialless
Documentation:
Enables Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless.
https://github.com/mikewest/credentiallessness
TODO(https://crbug.com/1175099): Remove one week after M96: 2021-11-25

Name: kCrossOriginOpenerPolicy
Documentation:
Enables Cross-Origin Opener Policy (COOP).
https://gist.github.com/annevk/6f2dd8c79c77123f39797f6bdac43f3e
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#cross-origin-opener-policy
Currently this feature is enabled for all platforms except WebView.

Name: kCrossOriginOpenerPolicyByDefault
Documentation:
Shift's COOP's default from `unsafe-none` to `same-origin-allow-popups`.
https://github.com/mikewest/coop-by-default/

Name: kCrossOriginWebAssemblyModuleSharingEnabled
Documentation: Enable cross-origin sharing of WebAssembly modules.

Name: kCssSelectorFragmentAnchor
Documentation: Enables CSS selector fragment anchors. https://crbug.com/1252460

Name: kCustomizedTabLoadTimeout
Documentation:
Enables using customized value for tab load timeout. This is used by session
restore in finch experiment to see what timeout value is better. The default
timeout is used when this feature is disabled.

Name: kDCompTripleBufferRootSwapChain
Documentation: Use BufferCount of 3 for the direct composition root swap chain.

Name: kDCompTripleBufferVideoSwapChain
Documentation: Use BufferCount of 3 for direct composition video swap chains.

Name: kDarkenWebsitesCheckboxInThemesSetting
Documentation: Enables auto dark feature in theme settings.

Name: kDataReductionProxyLowMemoryDevicePromo
Documentation: Enables the data saver promo for low memory Android devices.

Name: kDataSaverHoldback
Documentation:
Puts save-data header in the holdback mode. This disables sending of
save-data header to origins, and to the renderer processes within Chrome.

Name: kDawn2dCanvas
Documentation: Enables Dawn-accelerated 2D canvas.

Name: kDebounceDocumentProvider
Documentation: Feature to debounce drive requests from the document provider.

Name: kDebugHistoryInterventionNoUserActivation
Documentation: Enable debugging the issue crbug.com/1201355

Name: kDecodeJpeg420ImagesToYUV
Documentation:
Decodes jpeg 4:2:0 formatted images to YUV instead of RGBX and stores in this
format in the image decode cache. See crbug.com/919627 for details on the
feature.

Name: kDecodeLossyWebPImagesToYUV
Documentation:
Decodes lossy WebP images to YUV instead of RGBX and stores in this format
in the image decode cache. See crbug.com/900264 for details on the feature.

Name: kDefaultANGLEMetal
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's Metal backend.

Name: kDefaultANGLEOpenGL
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's OpenGL backend

Name: kDefaultANGLEVulkan
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's Vulkan backend.

Name: kDefaultEnableANGLEValidation
Documentation: Enables the use of ANGLE validation for non-WebGL contexts.

Name: kDefaultEnableGpuRasterization
Documentation:
Enable GPU Rasterization by default. This can still be overridden by
--enable-gpu-rasterization or --disable-gpu-rasterization.
DefaultEnableGpuRasterization has launched on Mac, Windows, ChromeOS, and
Android.

Name: kDefaultEnableOopRasterization
Documentation:
Enable out of process rasterization by default.  This can still be overridden
by --disable-oop-rasterization.

Name: kDefaultPassthroughCommandDecoder
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kDefaultTypedNavigationsToHttps
Documentation: Navigation experiments.

Name: kDeferRecyclingOfSyncTabNodesIfUnsynced
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/882489): Remove feature toggle during code cleanup when a
satisfying solution is found for closed tabs.

Name: kDelayFirstParkingOfStrings
Documentation:
Enabling this will delay the first aging of strings by 60 seconds instead of
the default. See comment around the use of the feature for the logic behind
the delay.

Name: kDelayLowPriorityRequestsAccordingToNetworkState
Documentation:
If enabled, the ResourceLoadScheculer will take the current network state
into consideration, when it plans to delay a low-priority throttleable
requests in the tight mode. The factors include:
 - The total number of the in-flight multiplexed connections (e.g.,
   H2/SPDY/QUIC).
 - HTTP RTT estimate.

Name: kDelayRequestsOnMultiplexedConnections
Documentation:
When kPriorityRequestsDelayableOnSlowConnections is enabled, HTTP
requests fetched from a SPDY/QUIC/H2 proxies can be delayed by the
ResourceScheduler just as HTTP/1.1 resources are. However, requests from such
servers are not subject to kMaxNumDelayableRequestsPerHostPerClient limit.

Name: kDelayUnsafeAds
Documentation:
Enables the artificial delaying of ads that are considered unsafe (e.g. http
or same-domain to the top-level).

Name: kDelayedWarnings
Documentation: Controls whether the delayed warning experiment is enabled.

Name: kDeleteExpiredDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete expired download.

Name: kDeleteOverwrittenDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete downloads that are overwritten by others.

Name: kDeprioritizeDOMTimersDuringPageLoading
Documentation: Deprioritizes JS timer tasks during a particular phase of page loading.

Name: kDesktopCaptureChangeSource
Documentation: Enable changing source dynamically for desktop capture.

Name: kDesktopDetailedLanguageSettings
Documentation: This feature enables setting the application language on Desktop.

Name: kDesktopPWAsAdditionalWindowingControls
Documentation: API that allows PWAs manually minimizing, maximizing and restoring windows.

Name: kDesktopPWAsCacheDuringDefaultInstall
Documentation:
When installing default installed PWAs, we wait for service workers
to cache resources.

Name: kDesktopPWAsElidedExtensionsMenu
Documentation:
Moves the Extensions "puzzle piece" icon from the title bar into the app menu
for web app windows.

Name: kDesktopPWAsFlashAppNameInsteadOfOrigin
Documentation:
Replaces the origin text flash in web app titlebars with the name of
the app.

Name: kDesktopPWAsNotificationIconAndTitle
Documentation:
Replaces the origin text flash and the icon in web app notifications with
the name of the app and the icon of the app.

Name: kDesktopPWAsRunOnOsLogin
Documentation: Enables or disables Desktop PWAs to be auto-started on OS login.

Name: kDesktopPWAsSubApps
Documentation:
API that allows installed PWAs to add additional shortcuts by means of
installing sub app components.

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStrip
Documentation:
Adds a tab strip to PWA windows.
TODO(crbug.com/897314): Enable this feature.

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStripLinkCapturing
Documentation:
Makes user navigations via links within web app scopes get captured tab
tabbed app windows.
TODO(crbug.com/897314): Enable this feature.

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStripSettings
Documentation: Adds a user settings that allows PWAs to be opened with a tab strip.

Name: kDesktopPWAsWebBundles
Documentation: Adds support for web bundles, making web apps able to be launched offline.

Name: kDesktopRestructuredLanguageSettings
Documentation:
This feature enables the desktop version's redesigned language settings
layout.

Name: kDesktopScreenshots
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable the screenshots feature, currently accessed only
through the sharing hub.

Name: kDestroyProfileOnBrowserClose
Documentation:
Destroy profiles when their last browser window is closed, instead of when
the browser exits.

Name: kDetailedLanguageSettings
Documentation: This feature enables setting the application language on Android.

Name: kDetectFormSubmissionOnFormClear
Documentation:
Enables submission detection for forms dynamically cleared but not removed
from the page.

Name: kDetectTargetEmbeddingLookalikes
Documentation: This feature enables interstitial warnings for target embedding lookalikes.

Name: kDetectedSourceLanguageOption
Documentation:
This feature renames the "Unknown" source language option to "Detected
Language" and enables translation of unknown source language pages on
Android.

Name: kDevicePosture
Documentation:
Enable the device posture API.
Tracking bug for enabling device posture API: https://crbug.com/1066842.

Name: kDialogFocusNewSpecBehavior
Documentation:
When <dialog>s are closed, this focuses the "previously focused" element
which had focus when the <dialog> was first opened.
TODO(crbug.com/649162): Remove DialogFocusNewSpecBehavior after
the feature is in stable with no issues.

Name: kDirectCompositionForceFullDamage
Documentation:
Forces Chrome's main backbuffer to full damage if the actual damage
is large enough and allows DWM to consider the main backbuffer as an
an overlay candidate.

Name: kDirectCompositionLowLatencyPresentation
Documentation: Use presentation feedback event queries (must be enabled) to limit latency.

Name: kDirectCompositionSoftwareOverlays
Documentation:
Allow overlay swapchain to present on all GPUs even if they only support
software overlays. GPU deny lists limit it to NVIDIA only at the moment.

Name: kDirectSockets
Documentation: Enables the Direct Sockets API.

Name: kDisableCGIParamMatching
Documentation: If enabled, suggestions from a cgi param name match are scored to 0.

Name: kDisableDeJelly
Documentation:
Kill-switch to disable de-jelly, even if flags/properties indicate it should
be enabled.

Name: kDisableFairJobScheduling
Documentation:
Under this feature, JobTaskSource doesn't use worker count in its sort key
such that worker threads are not distributed among running jobs equally.

Name: kDisableHttpDiskCache
Documentation: Tries disabling the HTTP disk cache.

Name: kDisableJobUpdatePriority
Documentation: Under this feature, priority update on Jobs is disabled.

Name: kDisableJobYield
Documentation: Under this feature, ThreadPool::ShouldYield() always returns false

Name: kDisableKeepaliveFetch
Documentation:
https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#request-keepalive-flag). This is introduced
for investigation on the memory usage, and should not be enabled widely.

Name: kDisablePrioritizedPostMessageForwarding
Documentation:
Killswitch for prioritizing cross-process postMessage forwarding.

TODO(crbug.com/1212894): Remove after M95.

Name: kDisableProcessReuse
Documentation:
When enabled, OOPIFs will not try to reuse compatible processes from
unrelated tabs.

Name: kDiscardCodeCacheAfterFirstUse
Documentation:
When enabled, frees up CachedMetadata after consumption by script resources
and modules. Needed for the experiment in http://crbug.com/1045052.

Name: kDiscardableMemoryBackingTrial
Documentation: Feature flag enabling the discardable memory backing trial.

Name: kDiscoFeedEndpoint
Documentation: Use the new DiscoFeed endpoint.

Name: kDispatchBeforeUnloadOnFreeze
Documentation:
When enabled, the beforeunload handler is dispatched when a frame is frozen.
This allows the browser to know whether discarding the frame could result in
lost user data, at the cost of extra CPU usage. The feature will be removed
once we have determine whether the CPU cost is acceptable.

Name: kDisplayLocking
Documentation: Enable Display Locking JavaScript APIs.

Name: kDisplayTitleForCurrentUrl
Documentation: Feature used to display the title of the current URL match.

Name: kDnsHttpssvc
Documentation:
Enables DNS query-only experiments for HTTPSSVC or INTEGRITY records,
depending on feature parameters. Received responses never affect Chrome
behavior other than metrics.

Not to be confused with `kUseDnsHttpsSvcb` which is querying HTTPS in order
to affect Chrome connection behavior.

Name: kDnsOverHttps
Documentation: Enable DNS over HTTPS (DoH).

Name: kDnsOverHttpsUpgrade
Documentation: Enable usage of hardcoded DoH upgrade mapping for use in automatic mode.

Name: kDnsTransactionDynamicTimeouts
Documentation:
Support for altering the parameters used for DNS transaction timeout. See
ResolveContext::SecureTransactionTimeout().

Name: kDocumentPolicy
Documentation: Enable document policy for configuring and restricting feature behavior.

Name: kDocumentPolicyNegotiation
Documentation: Enable document policy negotiation mechanism.

Name: kDocumentProvider
Documentation: Document provider

Name: kDocumentProviderAso
Documentation:
Feature to determine a value in the drive request indicating whether the
request should be served by the  ASO backend.

Name: kDocumentTransition
Documentation:
When enabled, permits shared/root element transitions. See
https://github.com/WICG/shared-element-transitions.

Name: kDocumentTransitionRenderer
Documentation:
When enabled, uses the code-path to drive shared/root element transitions
from the renderer process.

Name: kDontSendKeyEventsToJavascript
Documentation:
When enabled, this feature prevent blink sending key event to web unless it
is on installed PWA.

Name: kDownRankJustInTimePaymentApp
Documentation:
If enabled, just-in-time installable payment handlers are ranked lower than
complete autofill instruments in payment sheet's method selection section.

Name: kDownloadAutoResumptionNative
Documentation: Whether download auto-resumptions are enabled in native.

Name: kDownloadLater
Documentation: Whether to enable download later feature.

Name: kDownloadRange
Documentation: Arbitrary range request support for download system.

Name: kDownloadServiceFeature
Documentation:
Used to set configuration of download service through Finch. This is not used
to turn on/off the feature.

Name: kDurationEstimatesInCompositorTimingHistory
Documentation:
When enabled, CompositorTimingHistory will directly record the timing history
that is used to calculate main thread timing estimates, and use the
percentile of sum of different stages instead of the sum of percentiles.

Name: kDynamicBufferQueueAllocation
Documentation:
On platform and configuration where viz controls the allocation of frame
buffers (ie SkiaOutputDeviceBufferQueue is used), allocate and release frame
buffers on demand.

Name: kDynamicColorGamut
Documentation:
When wide color gamut content from the web is encountered, promote our
display to wide color gamut if supported.

Name: kDynamicMaxAutocomplete
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions to a dynamic limit based on how many URLs
would be shown. E.g., show up to 10 suggestions if doing so would display no
URLs; else show up to 8 suggestions if doing so would include 1 or more URLs.

Name: kDynamicSchedulerForClients
Documentation: User to parameterize adjustments to clients' deadlines.

Name: kDynamicSchedulerForDraw
Documentation: Used by Viz to parameterize adjustments to scheduler deadlines.

Name: kEagerCacheStorageSetupForServiceWorkers
Documentation:
Enable eagerly setting up a CacheStorage interface pointer and
passing it to service workers on startup as an optimization.
TODO(crbug/1077916): Re-enable once the issue with COOP/COEP is fixed.

Name: kEarlyCodeCache
Documentation: Enables fetching the code cache earlier in navigation.

Name: kEarlyEstablishGpuChannel
Documentation: Enable establishing the GPU channel early in renderer startup.

Name: kEarlyHintsPreloadForNavigation
Documentation: Enable Early Hints subresource preloads for navigation.

Name: kEarlyLibraryLoad
Documentation: Enable loading native libraries earlier in startup on Android.

Name: kEditPasswordsInSettings
Documentation: Enables the editing of passwords in Chrome settings.

Name: kEditingNG
Documentation: Enable EditingNG by default. This feature is for a kill switch.

Name: kElasticOverscroll
Documentation: Cached in Java as well, make sure defaults are updated together.

Name: kElidePrioritizationOfPreNativeBootstrapTasks
Documentation:
Under this flag Java bootstrap (aka startup) tasks that are run before native
initialization will not be specially prioritized by being posted at the front
of the Looper's queue.

Name: kElideTabPreloadAtStartup
Documentation:
Under this flag tab preloading at startup will be elided (i.e., not
performed).

Name: kEmbeddingRequiresOptIn
Documentation:
Requires documents embedded via <iframe>, etc, to explicitly opt-into the
embedding: https://github.com/mikewest/embedding-requires-opt-in.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityAriaVirtualContent
Documentation: Enable recognizing "aria-virtualcontent" as a valid aria property.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityExposeDisplayNone
Documentation: Enable exposing "display: none" nodes to the browser process AXTree

Name: kEnableAccessibilityExposeHTMLElement
Documentation:
Enable exposing the <html> element to the browser process AXTree
(as an ignored node).

Name: kEnableAccessibilityExposeIgnoredNodes
Documentation:
Enable exposing ignored nodes from Blink to the browser process AXTree.
This will allow us to simplify logic by eliminating the distiction between
"ignored and included in the tree" from "ignored and not included in the
tree".

Name: kEnableAccessibilityLanguageDetection
Documentation:
Enable language detection to determine language used in page text, exposed
on the browser process AXTree.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityTreeForViews
Documentation:
Serializes accessibility information from the Views tree and deserializes it
into an AXTree in the browser process.

Name: kEnableAggregatedMlSearchRanking
Documentation:
Enables using aggregated model in ranking non-app results for
non empty queries.

Name: kEnableAllSystemWebApps
Documentation:
Enables all registered system web apps, regardless of their respective
feature flags.

Name: kEnableAppListLaunchRecording
Documentation: Enables hashed recording of a app list launches.

Name: kEnableAppRanker
Documentation: Enable app ranking models.

Name: kEnableAppReinstallZeroState
Documentation:
Enables the feature to include a single reinstallation candidate in
zero-state.

Name: kEnableAriaElementReflection
Documentation:
Enable support for ARIA element reflection, for example
element.ariaActiveDescendantElement = child;

Name: kEnableAssistantSearch
Documentation: Enables the Assistant search redirection in the app list.

Name: kEnableAutomaticSnooze
Documentation:
A feature for enabling automatic snooze mode for In-Product Help (IPH). When
this flag is enabled, we don't show snooze button/UI on the IPH, but on
dismiss we will implicitly snooze it until the snooze limit count is reached.

Name: kEnableBrowsingDataLifetimeManager
Documentation:
Enable BrowsingDataLifetimeManager that periodically delete browsing data as
defined by the BrowsingDataLifetime policy.

Name: kEnableCanvas2DLayers
Documentation: Enables canvas 2d methods BeginLayer and EndLayer.

Name: kEnableCanvasContextLostInBackground
Documentation: Enables canvas context to clear context when it's running in background.

Name: kEnableExactMatchForNonLatinLocale
Documentation: Enables using exact string search for non latin locales.

Name: kEnableFuzzyAppSearch
Documentation: Enables using the fuzzy search algorithm for app search provider.

Name: kEnableGrShaderCacheForVulkan
Documentation: Enable GrShaderCache to use with Vulkan backend.

Name: kEnableHardwareMirrorMode
Documentation:
A temporary flag to control hardware mirroring until it is decided whether to
permanently remove hardware mirroring support. See crbug.com/1161556 for
details.

Name: kEnableLauncherSearchNormalization
Documentation: Enables normalization of search results in the launcher.

Name: kEnableManualPasswordGeneration
Documentation:
Enables UI that allows the user to create a strong password even if the field
wasn't parsed as a new password field.
TODO(crbug/1181254): Remove once it's launched.

Name: kEnableMediaInternals
Documentation: TODO(crbug.com/1146594): Flip this to disabled in M92.

Name: kEnableNewCanvas2DAPI
Documentation:
Enables new canvas 2d api features. Enabled either with either
enable-experimental-canvas-features or new-canvas-2d-api runtime flags

Name: kEnableOpenInNewTabFromStartSurfaceFeed
Documentation:
Feature that causes the "open in new tab" menu item to appear on feed items
on Start Surface.

Name: kEnableOverwritingPlaceholderUsernames
Documentation:
Enables the overwriting of prefilled username fields if the server predicted
the field to contain a placeholder value.

Name: kEnablePasswordsAccountStorage
Documentation:
Enables a second, Gaia-account-scoped password store for users who are signed
in but not syncing.

Name: kEnablePenetratingImageSelection
Documentation:
Allow image context menu selections to penetrate through transparent
elements.

Name: kEnablePerfettoClientApiProducer
Documentation:
Controls whether trace points are implemented using Perfetto's client library
(enabled) or legacy TraceLog (disabled).

Name: kEnablePersistentFilesystemInIncognito
Documentation: Enables persistent Filesystem API in incognito mode.

Name: kEnableQueryBasedMixedTypesRanker
Documentation: Enable a model that ranks query based non-apps result.

Name: kEnableRemovingAllThirdPartyCookies
Documentation: Enable removal of all third-party cookies and site data.

Name: kEnableRestrictedWebApis
Documentation: Enable the restricted web APIs for high-trusted apps.

Name: kEnableSaveDataHeader
Documentation:
Disable special treatment on requests with keepalive set (see
Enable save-data header seprately, without enabled data reduction service

Name: kEnableSuggestedFiles
Documentation: Enables Drive file suggestions in the suggestion chips.

Name: kEnableSuggestedLocalFiles
Documentation: Enables local file suggestions in the suggestion chips.

Name: kEnableTLS13EarlyData
Documentation: Enables TLS 1.3 early data.

Name: kEnableTabMuting
Documentation: Enables user control over muting tab audio from the tab strip.

Name: kEnableUserCloudSigninRestrictionPolicyFetcher
Documentation:
Enable the UserCloudSigninRestrictionPolicyFetcher to get the
ManagedAccountsSigninRestriction policy for a dasher account.

Name: kEnableVkPipelineCache
Documentation: Enable persistent storage of VkPipelineCache data.

Name: kEnableWALModeByDefault
Documentation: Enable WAL mode for all SQLite databases.

Name: kEnableWebAppUninstallFromOsSettings
Documentation: Enable web app uninstallation from Windows settings or control panel.

Name: kEnableZeroStateAppsRanker
Documentation:
Enable a model that ranks zero-state apps search result.
TODO(crbug.com/989350): This flag can be removed once the
AppSearchResultRanker is removed. Same with the
AppSearchResultRankerPredictorName.

Name: kEnableZeroStateMixedTypesRanker
Documentation: Enable a model that ranks zero-state files and recent queries.

Name: kEncryptedClientHello
Documentation:
Enables the TLS Encrypted ClientHello feature.
https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-ietf-tls-esni-13

TODO(https://crbug.com/1091403): This flag does not currently do much yet.
ECH is still in development.

Name: kEnforceFullDelegation
Documentation: Used to reject the apps with partial delegation.

Name: kEnterpriseConnectorsEnabled
Documentation:
Controls whether the Enterprise Connectors policies should be read by
ConnectorsManager.

Name: kEnterpriseReportingExtensionManifestVersion
Documentation:
Causes extension manifest versions to be included in the extension info
section of CBCM reports.

Name: kEnumerateDevicesHideDeviceIDs
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled and device permission is not granted by the user,
media-device enumeration will provide at most one device per type and the
device IDs will not be available.
TODO(crbug.com/1019176): remove the feature in M89.

Name: kExpectCTPruning
Documentation: Enables limiting the size of Expect-CT table.

Name: kExpectCTReporting
Documentation:
Enables Expect CT reporting, which sends reports for opted-in sites
that don't serve sufficient Certificate Transparency information.

Name: kExperimentalContentSecurityPolicyFeatures
Documentation:
Content counterpart of ExperimentalContentSecurityPolicyFeatures in
third_party/blink/renderer/platform/runtime_enabled_features.json5. Enables
experimental Content Security Policy features ('navigate-to' and
'prefetch-src').

Name: kExperimentalFlingAnimation
Documentation:
Enables the use of a touch fling curve that is based on the behavior of
native apps on Windows.

Name: kExperimentalKeywordMode
Documentation:
Feature used to enable various experiments on keyword mode, UI and
suggestions.

Name: kExplicitLanguageAsk
Documentation:
The feature that enables explicitly asking for user preferred
Accept-Languages on second run on Android. Replaced by kAppLanguagePrompt.

Name: kExposeSwDecodersToWebRTC
Documentation:
If enabled, when RTCVideoDecoderAdapter is used then SW decoders will be
exposed directly to WebRTC.

Name: kExtensionTelemetry
Documentation:
Enables collection of signals related to extension activity and uploads
of telemetry reports to SB servers.

Name: kExtensionWorkflowJustification
Documentation:
Controls whether the user justification text field is visible on the
extension request dialog.

Name: kExternalClearKeyForTesting
Documentation:
Enables support for External Clear Key (ECK) key system for testing on
supported platforms. On platforms that do not support ECK, this feature has
no effect.

Name: kExternalExtensionDefaultButtonControl
Documentation:
If enabled, this feature's |kExternalInstallDefaultButtonKey| field trial
parameter value controls which |ExternalInstallBubbleAlert| button is the
default.

Name: kExtraCookieValidityChecks
Documentation:
When enabled, additional cookie-related APIs will perform cookie field size
and character set validation to enforce stricter conformance with RFC6265bis.
TODO(crbug.com/1243852) Eventually enable this permanently and remove the
feature flag, assuming no breakage occurs with it enabled.

Name: kExtraSafelistedRequestHeadersForOutOfBlinkCors
Documentation: Extra CORS safelisted headers. See https://crbug.com/999054.

Name: kEyeDropper
Documentation: Used to enable the eye-dropper in the refresh color-picker.

Name: kFFmpegDecodeOpaqueVP8
Documentation: Prefer FFmpeg to LibVPX for Vp8 decoding with opaque alpha mode.

Name: kFailUrlProvisionFetcherForTesting
Documentation:
Prevents UrlProvisionFetcher from making a provisioning request. If
specified, any provisioning request made will not be sent to the provisioning
server, and the response will indicate a failure to communicate with the
provisioning server.

Name: kFallbackAfterDecodeError
Documentation:
Falls back to other decoders after audio/video decode error happens. The
implementation may choose different strategies on when to fallback. See
DecoderStream for details. When disabled, playback will fail immediately
after a decode error happens. This can be useful in debugging and testing
because the behavior is simpler and more predictable.

Name: kFastSolidColorDraw
Documentation: Uses glClear to composite solid color quads whenever possible.

Name: kFeatureNotificationGuide
Documentation: Main feature flag for the feature notification guide feature.

Name: kFedCm
Documentation: Enables JavaScript API to intermediate federated identity requests.

Name: kFederatedLearningOfCohorts
Documentation:
The main floc feature for all the subsidiary control and setting params. It's
controlling the floc update rate, and the minimum history domain size
required.
TODO(yaoxia): merge other floc features into this one.

Name: kFeedBackToTop
Documentation:
Feature that enables showing a callout to help users return to the top of the
feeds quickly.

Name: kFeedClearImageMemoryCache
Documentation:
Feature that enables clearing the image memory cache when the feed is
destroyed.

Name: kFeedImageMemoryCacheSizePercentage
Documentation:
Feature that allows tuning the size of the image memory cache. Value is a
percentage of the maximum size calculated for the device.

Name: kFeedInteractiveRefresh
Documentation: Feature that enables refreshing feeds triggered by the users.

Name: kFeedLoadingPlaceholder
Documentation:
Feature that shows placeholder cards instead of a loading spinner at first
load.

Name: kFeedSignInPromoDismiss
Documentation:
Feature that enables the 'X' in the signin promo in the Feed. Without the 'X'
the signin promo is not dismissible without opting to sign in.

Name: kFeedStamp
Documentation: Feature that enables StAMP cards in the feed.

Name: kFencedFrames
Documentation:
Enable the <fencedframe> element; see crbug.com/1123606. Note that enabling
this feature does not automatically expose this element to the web, it only
allows the element to be enabled by the runtime enabled feature, for origin
trials.

Name: kFileHandlingAPI
Documentation: File handling integration. https://crbug.com/829689

Name: kFileHandlingIcons
Documentation: File handling icons. https://crbug.com/1218213

Name: kFileSystemAccessPersistentPermissions
Documentation: Enables persistent permissions for the File System Access API.

Name: kFileSystemConnectorEnabled
Documentation: Experimental flag to enable or disable the file system connector.

Name: kFileTypePoliciesTag
Documentation: Determines the tag to pass to Omaha to get a file type policy.

Name: kFillOnAccountSelect
Documentation:
Enables the experiment for the password manager to only fill on account
selection, rather than autofilling on page load, with highlighting of fields.

Name: kFillingAcrossAffiliatedWebsites
Documentation:
Enables filling password on a website when there is saved password on
affiliated website.

Name: kFilterAdsOnAbusiveSites
Documentation: Enables the blocking of ads on sites that are abusive.

Name: kFilteringScrollPrediction
Documentation:
Enables filtering of predicted scroll events on compositor thread.
Uses the kFilterName* values in ui_base_features.h as the 'filter' feature
param.

Name: kFirstInputDelayWithoutEventListener
Documentation: Record FID even when there's no event listener.

Name: kFirstPartySets
Documentation: Enables usage of First Party Sets to determine cookie availability.

Name: kFirstPartySetsV2ComponentFormat
Documentation:
When enabled, the client will opt in to the V2 component format for the
First-Party Sets component.

Name: kFledge
Documentation: FLEDGE ad serving runtime flag/JS API.

Name: kFlocBypassIPIsPubliclyRoutableCheck
Documentation:
If enabled, the check for whether the IP address is publicly routable will be
bypassed when determining the eligibility for a page to be included in floc
computation. This is useful for developers to test FLoC in local environment.

Name: kFlocIdComputedEventLogging
Documentation:
Enables or disables the FlocIdComputed event logging, which happens when a
floc id is first computed for a browsing session or is refreshed due to a
long period of time has passed since the last computation.

Name: kFlocPagesWithAdResourcesDefaultIncludedInFlocComputation
Documentation:
If enabled, pages that had ad resources will be included in floc computation;
otherwise, only pages that used the document.interestCohort API will be
included. This flag affects a bit to be stored at page viewing time, so it
may take a full computation cycle for the floc to meet the configured
criteria.

Name: kFocusFollowsCursor
Documentation: Enables focus follow follow cursor (sloppyfocus).

Name: kFontAccess
Documentation: Font enumeration and data access. https://crbug.com/535764

Name: kFontAccessPersistent
Documentation: Font enumeration and data access. https://crbug.com/1173275

Name: kFontManagerEarlyInit
Documentation:
Whether to initialize the font manager when the renderer starts on a
background thread.

Name: kFontSrcLocalMatching
Documentation:
Enables fixes for matching src: local() for web fonts correctly against full
font name or postscript name. Rolling out behind a flag, as enabling this
enables a font indexer on Android which we need to test in the field first.

Name: kForceAppLanguagePrompt
Documentation: This feature forces the app UI prompt even if it has already been shown.

Name: kForceDisableExtendedSyncPromos
Documentation: This feature disables all extended sync promos.

Name: kForceFieldTrialSetupCrashForTesting
Documentation:
A testing feature that forces a crash during field trial creation
on developer and test builds.

Name: kForceHardwareAudioDecoders
Documentation:
Forces use of hardware (platform) audio decoders in
`media::DecoderSelector`.

Name: kForceHardwareVideoDecoders
Documentation:
Forces use of hardware (platform) video decoders in
`media::DecoderSelector`.

Name: kForceMajorVersion100InUserAgent
Documentation:
If enabled, the major version number returned by Chrome will be forced to
100.  This feature is only applicable for M96-M99 and will be removed after
M99.  The purpose of this feature is to allow users to test and proactively
fix any issues as we approach a 3-digit major version number.

Name: kForceMinorVersion100InUserAgent
Documentation:
If enabled, the minor version number returned by Chrome will be forced to
100.  This feature is only applicable for M96-M99 and will be removed after
M99.  The purpose of this feature is to allow testing of mitigation
strategies for conveying the major version number in the minor version string
if we decide to freeze the major version at 99.

Name: kForceShowContinueSection
Documentation:
Forces the launcher to show the continue section even if there are no file
suggestions.

Name: kForceStartupSigninPromo
Documentation: Features to trigger the startup sign-in promo at boot.

Name: kForceWebContentsDarkMode
Documentation: Automatically convert light-themed pages to use a Blink-generated dark theme

Name: kForcedColors
Documentation: Used to enable forced colors mode for web content.

Name: kFractionalScrollOffsets
Documentation:
Enables scrollers inside Blink to store scroll offsets in fractional
floating-point numbers rather than truncating to integers.

Name: kFrameExperimentOnlyWhenLoading
Documentation:
Used along with |kLowPriorityForHiddenFrame|,
|kLowPriorityForSubFrameThrottleableTask|, |kLowPriorityForThrottleableTask|,
|kLowPriorityForSubFrame| to enable one of these experiments only during the
load use case.

Name: kFreezeBackgroundTabOnNetworkIdle
Documentation:
Freeze scheduler task queues in background on network idle.
This feature only works if stop-in-background is enabled.

Name: kFreezePurgeMemoryAllPagesFrozen
Documentation: Perform memory purges after freezing only if all pages are frozen.

Name: kFrequencyCappingForLargeStickyAdDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting large sticky ads.
Large-sticky-ads are those ads that stick to the bottom of the page
regardless of a user’s efforts to scroll, and take up more than 30% of the
screen’s real estate.

Name: kFrequencyCappingForOverlayPopupDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting overlay popups. Overlay-popups
are the interstitials that pop up and block the main content of the page.

Name: kGPayAppDynamicUpdate
Documentation:
If enabled, the GooglePayPaymentApp handles communications between the native
GPay app and the browser for dynamic updates on shipping and payment data.

Name: kGWSPrefetchHoldback
Documentation: Preconnects instead of prefetching from GWS.

Name: kGav1VideoDecoder
Documentation: Use Gav1VideoDecoder to decode AV1 streams.

Name: kGenericSensorExtraClasses
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values
in the .cc file.

Name: kGeoLanguage
Documentation:
Controls whether the GeoLanguage system is enabled. GeoLanguage uses IP-based
coarse geolocation to provide an estimate (for use by other Chrome features
such as Translate) of the local/regional language(s) corresponding to the
device's location. If this feature is disabled, the GeoLanguage provider is
not initialized at startup, and clients calling it will receive an empty list
of languages.

Name: kGiveJavaUiThreadDefaultTaskTraitsUserBlockingPriority
Documentation:
Gives Java tasks that are posted with the UiThreadTaskTraits.DEFAULT traits
user-blocking priority rather than their default user-visible priority.
See crbug.com/1259560.

Name: kGlobalMediaControls
Documentation: Show toolbar button that opens dialog for controlling media sessions.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsAutoDismiss
Documentation: Auto-dismiss global media controls.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsForChromeOS
Documentation: Allow Global Media Controls in system tray of CrOS.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsModernUI
Documentation: Enable an updated version of the Global Media Controls UI.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsPictureInPicture
Documentation: Show picture-in-picture button in Global Media Controls.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsSeamlessTransfer
Documentation: Enable selection of audio output device in Global Media Controls.

Name: kGpuUseDisplayThreadPriority
Documentation: Use ThreadPriority::DISPLAY for GPU main, viz compositor and IO threads.

Name: kGreaseUACH
Documentation:
Determines if an extra brand version pair containing possibly escaped double
quotes and escaped backslashed should be added to the Sec-CH-UA header
(activated by kUserAgentClientHint)

Name: kHandwritingRecognitionWebPlatformApiFinch
Documentation:
Whether the HandwritingRecognition API can be enabled by origin trial.
Disabling this feature disables both the origin trial and the mojo interface.

Name: kHardwareMediaKeyHandling
Documentation: Enables handling of hardware media keys for controlling media.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryption
Documentation:
Enables hardware secure decryption if supported by hardware and CDM.
TODO(xhwang): Currently this is only used for development of new features.
Apply this to Android and ChromeOS as well where hardware secure decryption
is already available.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryptionExperiment
Documentation:
Same as `kHardwareSecureDecryption` above, but only enable experimental
sub key systems. Which sub key system is experimental is key system specific.

Name: kHeavyAdIntervention
Documentation:
Enables or disables the intervention that unloads ad iframes with intensive
resource usage.

Name: kHeavyAdInterventionWarning
Documentation:
Enables or disables reporting on the intervention that unloads ad iframes
with intensive resource usage.

Name: kHeavyAdPrivacyMitigations
Documentation:
Enables or disables the privacy mitigations for the heavy ad intervention.
This throttles the amount of interventions that can occur on a given host in
a time period. It also adds noise to the thresholds used. This is separate
from the intervention feature so it does not interfere with field trial
activation, as this blocklist is created for every user, and noise is decided
prior to seeing a heavy ad.

Name: kHideWebAppOriginText
Documentation: Hides the origin text from showing up briefly in WebApp windows.

Name: kHighPriorityBeforeUnload
Documentation:
Tells the RenderFrameHost to send beforeunload messages on a different
local frame interface which will handle the messages at a higher priority.

Name: kHighPriorityDatabaseTaskType
Documentation: Enable setting high priority database task type from field trial parameters.

Name: kHistoryPreventSandboxedNavigation
Documentation:
Prevents sandboxed iframes from using the history API to navigate frames
outside their subttree, if they are restricted from doing top-level
navigations.

Name: kHistoryQuickProviderAblateInMemoryURLIndexCacheFile
Documentation:
If enabled, the HistoryQuickProvider's InMemoryURLIndex service never
persists its index to a cache file on shutdown, and instead always rebuilds
it from the HistoryService on startup. Persisting the index to disk causes
over 10% of all shutdown hangs.

Name: kHlsPlayer
Documentation:
Enables the use of MediaPlayerRenderer for HLS playback. When disabled,
HLS manifests will fail to load (triggering source fallback or load error).

Name: kHttpsOnlyMode
Documentation: Sets whether the HTTPS-Only Mode setting is displayed in the settings UI.

Name: kHudDisplayForPerformanceMetrics
Documentation:
When enabled, cc will show blink's Web-Vital metrics inside its heads up
display.

Name: kIOSEnablePasswordManagerBrandingUpdate
Documentation:
Feature flag that updates icons, strings, and views for Google Password
Manager.

Name: kIPHDemoMode
Documentation: A feature for enabling a demonstration mode for In-Product Help (IPH).

Name: kIPHDummyFeature
Documentation: A feature to ensure all arrays can contain at least one feature.

Name: kIPHInWebUIDemo
Documentation: When enabled, shows a demo of in-product help in a WebUI context.

Name: kIPHSnooze
Documentation: A feature for enabling a snooze mode for In-Product Help (IPH).

Name: kIPv6Probing
Documentation: Enable IPv6 ping probes to RIPE DNS.

Name: kIdentifiabilityStudy
Documentation:
Root feature for all identifiability study logic.

If the feature is disabled, then this browser instance will not be
participating in the identifiability study. I.e. no identifiability metrics
will be recorded or reported.

Enabling the feature doesn't automatically make this client part of the study
either.

Name: kIdleDetection
Documentation:
This is intended as a kill switch for the Idle Detection feature. To enable
this feature, the experimental web platform features flag should be set,
or the site should obtain an Origin Trial token.

Name: kIgnoreSyncEncryptionKeysLongMissing
Documentation:
Causes Sync to ignore updates encrypted with keys that have been missing for
too long from this client; Sync will proceed normally as if those updates
didn't exist.

Name: kImageSearchSuggestionThumbnail
Documentation:
Feature to enable showing thumbnail in front of the Omnibox clipboard image
search suggestion.

Name: kImpulseScrollAnimations
Documentation:

Name: kIncludeIpcOverheadInNavigationStart
Documentation:
Historically most navigations required IPC from browser to renderer and
from renderer back to browser. This was done to check for before-unload
handlers on the current page and occurred regardless of whether a
before-unload handler was present. The navigation start time (as used in
various metrics) is the time the renderer initiates the IPC back to the
browser. If this feature is enabled, the navigation start time takes into
account the cost of the IPC from the browser to renderer. More specifically:
navigation_start = time_renderer_sends_ipc_to_browser -
   (time_renderer_receives_ipc - time_browser_sends_ipc)
Note that navigation_start does not take into account the amount of time the
renderer spends processing the IPC (that is, executing script).

Name: kIntensiveWakeUpThrottling
Documentation:
When enabled, wake ups from throttleable TaskQueues are limited to 1 per
minute in a page that has been backgrounded for 5 minutes.

Intensive wake up throttling is enforced in addition to other throttling
mechanisms:
 - 1 wake up per second in a background page or hidden cross-origin frame
 - 1% CPU time in a page that has been backgrounded for 10 seconds

Feature tracking bug: https://crbug.com/1075553

The base::Feature should not be read from; rather the provided accessors
should be used, which also take into account the managed policy override of
the feature.

The base::Feature is enabled by default on all platforms. However, on
Android, it has no effect because page freezing kicks in at the same time. It
would have an effect if the grace period ("grace_period_seconds" param) was
reduced.

for non-English locales (English locales are 'en' and 'en-GB').
This feature is only meaningful if `OmniboxPedalsBatch3` is enabled.

Name: kOmniboxPedalsTranslationConsole
Documentation: Feature that enables loading synonyms from the translation console.

Name: kOmniboxRemoveSuggestionsFromClipboard
Documentation: Feature used to allow users to remove suggestions from clipboard.

Name: kOmniboxSpareRenderer
Documentation: Spare renderer warmup for faster website loading.

Name: kOmniboxTabSwitchSuggestions
Documentation:
Please do not add more features to this "big blob" list.
Instead, use the categorized and alphabetized lists below this "big blob".
You can create a new category if none of the existing ones fit.

Name: kOmniboxTrendingZeroPrefixSuggestionsOnNTP
Documentation:
Used to enable/disable remote zero-prefix suggestions on the NTP
(Omnibox and NTP realbox). Enabling this feature permits the code to issue
suggestions request to the server on the new tab page for users who decided
not to sign in.

Name: kOmniboxTriggerForNoStatePrefetch
Documentation:
Enables omnibox trigger no state prefetch. Only one of
kOmniboxTriggerForPrerender2 or kOmniboxTriggerForNoStatePrefetch can be
enabled in the experiment.
TODO(crbug.com/1267731): Remove this flag once the experiments are completed.

Name: kOmniboxTriggerForPrerender2
Documentation:
This flag is used for enabling Omnibox triggered prerendering and
blink::WebRuntimeFeatures::Prerender2RelatedFeatures that enables Prerender2
related web exposed features. This flag takes effect only when
blink::features::Prerender2 is enabled. See crbug.com/1166085 for more
details of Omnibox triggered prerendering.

Name: kOnDemandAccessibilityEvents
Documentation:
Allows the use of an experimental feature to drop any AccessibilityEvents
that are not relevant to currently enabled accessibility services.

Name: kOnDeviceHeadProviderIncognito
Documentation: On Device Head Suggest.

Name: kOnFocusSuggestionsContextualWeb
Documentation:
Enables on-focus suggestions on the Open Web, that are contextual to the
current URL. Will only work if user is signed-in and syncing, or is
otherwise eligible to send the current page URL to the suggest server.

There's multiple flags here for multiple backend configurations:
 - Default (search queries)
 - SRP specific toggle (enables SRP on top of Web Pages for features below)
 - On-Content Suggestions

TODO(tommycli): It's confusing whether Contextual Web includes SRP or not.
`kOnFocusSuggestionsContextualWebAllowSRP` suggests it's included, but
`kClobberTriggersContextualWebZeroSuggest` suggests it's not. Make this
consistent, probably by renaming flags to distinguish between OTHER and SRP.

Name: kOobeMarketingAdditionalCountriesSupported
Documentation: Enables/disables marketing emails for other countries other than US,CA,UK.

Name: kOobeMarketingDoubleOptInCountriesSupported
Documentation: Enables/disables marketing emails for double opt-in countries.

Name: kOomIntervention
Documentation: Enables or disabled the OOM intervention.

Name: kOopRasterizationDDL
Documentation: Turns on skia deferred display list for out of process raster.

Name: kOptimizationGuideMetadataValidation
Documentation: Enables the validation of optimization guide metadata.

Name: kOptimizationGuideModelDownloading
Documentation: Enables the downloading of models.

Name: kOptimizationHints
Documentation:
Enables the syncing of the Optimization Hints component, which provides
hints for what optimizations can be applied on a page load.

Name: kOptimizationHintsFieldTrials
Documentation:
Feature flag that contains a feature param that specifies the field trials
that are allowed to be sent up to the Optimization Guide Server.

Name: kOptimizationTargetPrediction
Documentation: Enables the prediction of optimization targets.

Name: kOptimizeUpdateLoadInfo
Documentation: Optimize the implementation of calling URLLoaderFactory::UpdateLoadInfo().

Name: kOriginAgentClusterDefaultEnabled
Documentation:
If enabled, an absent Origin-Agent-Cluster: header is interpreted as
requesting an origin agent cluster, but in the same process.

Name: kOriginAgentClusterDefaultWarning
Documentation:
This flag enables a console warning in cases where document.domain is set
without origin agent clustering being explicitly disabled.
(This is a transitory behaviour on the road to perma-enabling
kOriginAgentClusterDefaultEnabled above.)

Name: kOriginIsolationHeader
Documentation:
Controls the Origin-Agent-Cluster header. Tracking bug
https://crbug.com/1042415; flag removal bug (for when this is fully launched)
https://crbug.com/1148057.

The name is "OriginIsolationHeader" because that was the old name when the
feature was under development.

Name: kOriginPolicy
Documentation: Origin Policy. See https://crbug.com/751996

Name: kOriginTrialsSampleAPIThirdPartyAlternativeUsage
Documentation:
Sample field trial feature for testing alternative usage restriction in
origin trial third party tokens.

Name: kOverlayFullscreenVideo
Documentation: Only used for disabling overlay fullscreen (aka SurfaceView) in Clank.

Name: kOverlayScrollbar
Documentation:
Enables or disables overlay scrollbars in Blink (i.e. web content) on Aura
or Linux.  The status of native UI overlay scrollbars is determined in
PlatformStyle::CreateScrollBar. Does nothing on Mac.

Name: kOverrideTranslateTriggerInIndia
Documentation:
This feature controls the activation of the experiment to trigger Translate
in India on English pages independent of the user's UI language. The params
associated with the experiment dictate which model is used to determine the
target language.

Name: kOverscrollHistoryNavigation
Documentation: History navigation in response to horizontal overscroll (aka gesture-nav).

Name: kPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables page content to be annotated.

Name: kPageInfoAboutThisSite
Documentation: Enables the "About this site" section in Page Info.

Name: kPageInfoHistory
Documentation: Enables the history sub page for Page Info.

Name: kPageInfoStoreInfo
Documentation: Enables the store info row for Page Info.

Name: kPageTextExtraction
Documentation:
This feature flag does not turn off any behavior, it is only used for
experiment parameters.

Name: kPaintHolding
Documentation:
Enable defer commits to avoid flash of unstyled content, for same origin
navigation only.

Name: kPaintHoldingCrossOrigin
Documentation:
Enable defer commits to avoid flash of unstyled content, for all navigation.
Disabled on Mobile to allow for a delayed Finch roll-out. Enabled on
Desktop platforms.

Name: kPaintPreviewDemo
Documentation:
Used to enable a main menu item on Android that captures and displays a paint
preview for the current page. The paint preview UI will be dismissed on back
press and all associated stored files deleted. This intended to test whether
capturing and playing paint preview works on a specific site.

Name: kPaintPreviewShowOnStartup
Documentation:
Used to enable the paint preview capture and show on startup for Android. If
enabled, paint previews for each tab are captured when a tab is hidden and
are deleted when a tab is closed. When a tab with a captured paint perview
is shown at startup and there is no cached page we will show the paint
preview.

Name: kParakeet
Documentation: PARAKEET ad serving runtime flag/JS API.

Name: kParallelDownloading
Documentation: Whether a download can be handled by parallel jobs.

Name: kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions connections based on the NetworkIsolationKey associated with a
request.

Name: kPartitionDomainReliabilityByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation: Partitions Domain Reliability beacons and upload by NetworkIsolationKey.

Name: kPartitionExpectCTStateByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions Expect-CT data by NetworkIsolationKey. This only affects the
Expect-CT data itself. Regardless of this value, reports will be uploaded
using the associated NetworkIsolationKey, when one's available.

This feature requires kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey,
kPartitionHttpServerPropertiesByNetworkIsolationKey, and
kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey to all be enabled to work.

Name: kPartitionHttpServerPropertiesByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions HttpServerProperties based on the NetworkIsolationKey associated
with a request.

Name: kPartitionNelAndReportingByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions Network Error Logging and Reporting API data by
NetworkIsolationKey. Also partitions all reports generated by other consumers
of the reporting API. Applies the NetworkIsolationKey to reports uploads as
well.

When disabled, the main entry points of the reporting and NEL services ignore
NetworkIsolationKey parameters, and they're cleared while loading from the
cache, but internal objects can be created with them (e.g., endpoints), for
testing.

Name: kPartitionSSLSessionsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions TLS sessions and QUIC server configs based on the
NetworkIsolationKey associated with a request.

This feature requires kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey to be
enabled to work.

Name: kPartitionedCookies
Documentation:
When enabled, sites can opt-in to having their cookies partitioned by
top-level site with the Partitioned attribute. Partitioned cookies will only
be sent when the browser is on the same top-level site that it was on when
the cookie was set.

Name: kPasswordBreachEventReporting
Documentation:
Enable reporting password leaks to the reporting connector when the Password
Manager's Leak Detector has found some compromised credentials.

Name: kPasswordChange
Documentation: Enables password change flow from leaked password dialog.

Name: kPasswordChangeInSettings
Documentation: Enables password change flow from bulk leak check in settings.

Name: kPasswordChangeOnlyRecentCredentials
Documentation:
Enables offering automated password change only for compromised credentials
that are recently used. Only has an effect if PasswordChangeInSettings is
also enabled.

Name: kPasswordImport
Documentation: Controls the ability to import passwords from Chrome's settings page.

Name: kPasswordProtectionForSignedInUsers
Documentation: Enable GAIA password protection for signed-in users.

Name: kPasswordReuseDetectionEnabled
Documentation: Enables password reuse detection.

Name: kPasswordScriptsFetching
Documentation: Enables password scripts fetching for the |PasswordChangeInSettings| feature.

Name: kPasswordsAccountStorageRevisedOptInFlow
Documentation: Enables a revised opt-in flow for the account-scoped password storage.

Name: kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P
Documentation:
When kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P is enabled, then a subset of
the browser initiated traffic may be paused if there is at least one active
P2P connection and the network is estimated to be congested. This feature is
intended to throttle only the browser initiated traffic that is expected to
be heavy (has large request/response sizes) when real time content might be
streaming over an active P2P connection.

Name: kPauseLowPriorityBrowserRequestsOnWeakSignal
Documentation:
When kPauseLowPriorityBrowserRequestsOnWeakSignal is enabled, then a subset
of the browser initiated requests may be deferred if the device is using
cellular connection and the signal quality is low. Android only.

Name: kPaymentHandlerPopUpSizeWindow
Documentation:
Desktop only, if enabled payment handler window size matches the pop up
window size.

Name: kPaymentRequestBasicCard
Documentation:
Enable the basic-card payment method from the PaymentRequest API. This flag
will be used to deprecate basic-card eventually: crbug.com/1209835.

Name: kPepper3DImageChromium
Documentation:
If Pepper 3D Image Chromium is allowed, this feature controls whether it is
enabled.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1196009): Remove this feature, remove the code that
uses it.

Name: kPepperCrossOriginRedirectRestriction
Documentation: Kill-switch to introduce a compatibility breaking restriction.

Name: kPercentBasedScrolling
Documentation:
Enables percent-based scrolling for mousewheel and keyboard initiated
scrolls.

Name: kPerformanceHintsObserver
Documentation: Exposed for testing.

Name: kPeriodicBackgroundSync
Documentation: Whether web apps can run periodic tasks upon network connectivity.

Name: kPermissionAuditing
Documentation:
Keep a client-side log of when websites access permission-gated capabilities
to allow the user to audit usage.

Name: kPermissionChip
Documentation:
Enables an experimental permission prompt that uses a chip in the location
bar.

Name: kPermissionChipGestureSensitive
Documentation:
When kPermissionChip (above) is enabled, controls whether or not the
permission chip should be more prominent when the request is associated with
a gesture. Does nothing when kPermissionChip is disabled.

Name: kPermissionChipIsProminentStyle
Documentation:
When kPermissionChip (above) is enabled, controls whether or not the
permission chip should be shown in the prominent style (white on blue) or in
the secondary style (blue on white).

Name: kPermissionChipRequestTypeSensitive
Documentation:
When kPermissionChip (above) is enabled, controls whether or not the
permission chip should be more or less prominent depending on the request
type. Does nothing when kPermissionChip is disabled.

Name: kPermissionGeolocationPredictions
Documentation: Enables using the prediction service for geolocation permission prompts.

Name: kPermissionPredictionServiceUseUrlOverride
Documentation:
When enabled, use the value of the `service_url` FeatureParam as the url
for the Web Permission Predictions Service.

Name: kPermissionPredictions
Documentation:
Enables using the prediction service for permission prompts. We will keep
this feature in order to allow us to update the holdback chance via finch.

Name: kPermissionQuietChip
Documentation:
Enables an experimental less prominent permission prompt that uses a chip in
the location bar. Requires chrome://flags/#quiet-notification-prompts to be
enabled.

Name: kPersistContextAnnotationsInHistoryDb
Documentation:
This flag is to enable us to turn on persisting context annotations WITHOUT
exposing the Memories UI in general. If EITHER this flag or `kJourneys` is
enabled, users will have context annotations persisted into their History DB.

Name: kPersistentHistogramsFeature
Documentation: Feature definition for enabling histogram persistence.

Name: kPersistentQuotaIsTemporaryQuota
Documentation: Makes Persistent quota the same as Temporary quota.

Name: kPictureInPicture
Documentation: Enable Picture-in-Picture.

Name: kPictureInPictureAPI
Documentation: Enable picture in picture web api for android.

Name: kPlaybackSpeedButton
Documentation: Display the playback speed button on the media controls.

Name: kPlzDedicatedWorker
Documentation:
Enable browser-initiated dedicated worker script loading
(PlzDedicatedWorker). https://crbug.com/906991

Name: kPlzServiceWorker
Documentation: Enable in-browser script loading for a brand new service worker.

Name: kPointerLockOptions
Documentation: Allows requesting unadjusted movement when entering pointerlock.

Name: kPolicyBlocklistThrottleRequiresPoliciesLoaded
Documentation: PolicyBlocklistThrottle defers navigations until policies are loaded.

Name: kPopularSitesBakedInContentFeature
Documentation:
This feature is enabled by default. Otherwise, users who need it would not
get the right configuration timely enough. The configuration affects only
Android or iOS users.

Name: kPortals
Documentation:
Enable Portals. https://crbug.com/865123.
Note that default enabling this does not expose the portal
element on its own, but does allow its use with an origin trial. This was the
case for the M85 Android only origin trial (https://crbug.com/1040212).

Name: kPortalsCrossOrigin
Documentation:
When kPortals is enabled, allow portals to load content that is third-party
(cross-origin) to the hosting page. Otherwise has no effect.

https://crbug.com/1013389

Name: kPostQuantumCECPQ2
Documentation: Enables CECPQ2, a post-quantum key-agreement, in TLS 1.3 connections.

Name: kPostQuantumCECPQ2SomeDomains
Documentation:
Enables CECPQ2, a post-quantum key-agreement, in TLS 1.3 connections for a
subset of domains. (This is intended as Finch kill-switch. For testing
compatibility with large ClientHello messages, use |kPostQuantumCECPQ2|.)

Name: kPreconnectToSearch
Documentation: Feature to control preconnect to search.

Name: kPredictivePrefetchingAllowedOnAllConnectionTypes
Documentation: Allows prediction operations (e.g., prefetching) on all connection types.

Name: kPreemptiveLinkToTextGeneration
Documentation: Enables link to text to be generated in advance.

Name: kPreferCompositingToLCDText
Documentation:
Whether we should composite a PLSA (paint layer scrollable area) even if it
